James Hayward, four, had his toy gun confiscated at East Midlands Airport .
He had arrived with his parents, Phil, 44, and Hazel, 38, for their flight .
But security officers took exception to James' harmless toy gun .
They demanded he hand it over and they demanded it be returned to family .
Mr Hayward said: 'It just seemed a bit ludicrous to take a plastic gun away from a child'